In[516]:
Q1= train_data["median_house_value"].quantile(0.25)
Q3= train_data["median_house_value"].quantile(0.75)

IQR = Q3 - Q1

low_fence = Q1 - (1.5 * IQR)
high_fence = Q3 + (1.5 * IQR)

print("Lower Fence: ",low_fence)
print("Higher Fence: ",high_fence)

print("Outliers above fence:", (train_data["median_house_value"] > high_fence).sum())

outliers = train_data[train_data["median_house_value"] >= high_fence].index
train_data.drop(outliers, axis=0, inplace=True)
train_data.count()
